<section class="project-content">
  <div class="summary">
    <h2>Reducing plastic waste in the Amazon with design</h2>
    <p class="summary-text">designed a manual for indigenous Amazonian communities to upcycle plastic water bottles into useful tools, toys and raw materials, including ceiling lights, joints, games and jewelry</p>
  </div>
  <div class="project-role">
    <h3>Context</h3>
    <p>three month project; two weeks field research with indigenous communities. our <a target=”_blank” href="https://3eeed6f4-f802-4461-9042-b0fbb17c7fc3.filesusr.com/ugd/0ec7ce_e36950ef1d5f434a9842db913aea108a.pdf">manual</a> is currently being used by Amazonian nonprofits in sustainability workshops</p>
    <h3 class="role">Role</h3>
    <p>design strategy, research and implementation</p>
    <p class="team">Team: three designers (Emi, Manon and I) in collaboration with our client, the Omacha Foundation and indigenous leaders in Puerto Narino, Colombia</p>
  </div>
</section>
